# Checklist YAML

- Top-level key is `checklist` with `name`, `version`, `domain`, `sections`.
- `metadata` supports `author`, `tags`, `estimated_time`.
- `variables` entries require `prompt`; `options` are strings; `default` is a string.
- Items require `id` and `check`; optional `severity`, `guidance`, `evidence_required`,
  `condition`, `matrix`.
- `severity` values are `low`, `medium`, `high`, `critical` (default `medium`).
- `matrix` entries are mappings of string -> string.
- `condition` supports simple boolean expressions (`==`, `!=`, `in`, `and`, `or`, `not`).
